Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain the
@Sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Drain the @Mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat
dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}. Preheat the #grill{} to high.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot,
add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams}, pepper chunks and corn. Stir-fry until
tender, ~{5-6%mins}.

Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic. Cook for ~{30%secs} more.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliter}.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%mins}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When ready, combine the cooked pasta and sauce (in whichever #pan{} is biggest).
Stir through the @Harissa Paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder).
Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an
appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Scatter over the mozzarella and Cheddar.

Pop the dish under the grill and cook until the cheese is bubbling and
golden, ~{7-8%mins}.

When ready, share the harissa pasta bake between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!